fields.Title: You: "How does that work?"
fields.Dialogue Text: How does that work?

fields.Title: You: "What's the pale?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What's the pale?

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "It is, and good for the circulation..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It is, and good for the circulation, too.

fields.Title: Logic: "That seems... improbable."
fields.Dialogue Text: That seems... improbable.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "This is exactly what you need!"
fields.Dialogue Text: This is exactly what you need!

fields.Title: You: "Look through the shelf."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look through the shelf.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "This bookstore is not *strictly* ab..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This bookstore is not *strictly* about crime, romance, and biographies of famous people -- there's also a wide range of paranatural literature.

fields.Title: Half Light: "I don't know... I don't want to be..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I don't know... I don't want to be the party-pooper, but this *pale territory* sounds sort of dangerous. Maybe you *shouldn't* walk in it naked.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "Various paranatural books still lit..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Various paranatural books still litter the shelf.

fields.Title: Plaisance: ""Indeed..." She mumbles, staring at..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Indeed..." She mumbles, staring at the book for a moment. "Something about that book does seem to have spoken to you..."

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "You sense something ominous emanati..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You sense something ominous emanating from the shelf... but it lacks form and substance, and soon enough you lose track of it.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "It is supposedly invigorating and g..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It is supposedly invigorating and good for the circulation.

fields.Title: You: "Fair enough. What else is in there?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Fair enough. What else is in there?

fields.Title: You: "Sounds painful."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sounds painful.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "Among other benefits, it is alleged..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Among other benefits, it is alleged to restore a damaged liver to perfect health.

fields.Title: You: ""All right. I want to buy *Medicina..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "All right. I want to buy *Medicinal Purposes of the Pale*."

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "For general health and well-being,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: For general health and well-being, readers are encouraged to take regular strolls through the pale, though a sidebar cautions readers to limit each stroll to less than an hour...

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "The book contains very little expla..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The book contains very little explanation on the matter -- this knowledge seems to be taken for granted.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "The point of the book, and many oth..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The point of the book, and many others on this shelf, is to give people medicinal advice in situations where they don't have access to paid health services.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "...there's even a chapter on the an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: ...there's even a chapter on the ancient Seraise tradition of using duck gall bladder (preservatives) to treat and prevent sexually transmitted diseases. Pre- and post-factum apply. Nothing worth buying.

fields.Title: Plaisance: ""Excuse me, sir! I believe you've b..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Excuse me, sir! I believe you've been *perusing* that particular volume long enough. If you'd like to continue reading I must insist you buy it."

fields.Title: You: "Find something truly otherworldly."
fields.Dialogue Text: Find something truly otherworldly.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "It also recommends consuming distil..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It also recommends consuming distilled spirits like vodka or whiskey that have been aged in the pale. Readers are instructed to cover these jars in a shallow hole just inside the pale, and leave them there for 30-60 days, depending on the potency desired.

fields.Title: You: "And what does this pale-aged liquor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: And what does this pale-aged liquor do?

fields.Title: You: "I should probably get my hands on s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I should probably get my hands on some of that. What else is in there?

fields.Title: You: "I think I've heard enough."
fields.Dialogue Text: I think I've heard enough.

fields.Title: You: "That's all I need to know."
fields.Dialogue Text: That's all I need to know.

fields.Title: You: ""Storekeep, what books are these?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Storekeep, what books are these?"

fields.Title: Plaisance: ""I can't have you end up... like......"
fields.Dialogue Text: "I can't have you end up... like... opening a police store next door and stealing my customers, oh no."

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "Amidst the various books you find o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Amidst the various books you find one written by someone named Matthias W. Dundas. It's about "Wholeness, Unity, Balance".

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: ""Wholeness, Unity, Balance" on the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Wholeness, Unity, Balance" on the other hand, can basically take care of anything. Though it is important to note...

fields.Title: Rhetoric: "These three things are very importa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: These three things are very important to the working-class mind.

fields.Title: You: "Uh huh, interesting."
fields.Dialogue Text: Uh huh, interesting.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "It serves platitudes, while also te..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It serves platitudes, while also telling everyone that traditional medicine (the kind people don't have access to, and which costs more than this book) is garbage, and would only give you cancer anyway, without even curing your cold or anything.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "The book features chapters on topic..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The book features chapters on topics such as: how to find magnesium (it even lists plants you can harvest magnesium from); how to continue drinking if you're an alcoholic who has destroyed his liver; and...

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "This is just mundane garbage. What'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: This is just mundane garbage. What's even para-natural about this?

fields.Title: You: "[Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: [Leave.]

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Even better if you can find someone..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even better if you can find someone else, preferably a large man dressed in nothing but a towel, to thrash you while you're spread naked and helpless on a cool slab.

fields.Title: Logic: "Entroponetic nudism? That's insane...."
fields.Dialogue Text: Entroponetic nudism? That's insane. That's beyond dangerous.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: ""When it's up to your mind to heal..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "When it's up to your mind to heal yourself, then it's because of your mind that you're *ill* in the first place."

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "The book contains descriptions of v..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The book contains descriptions of various pseudo-scientific therapies, alternative medicines, and folk remedies involving *the pale* -- also known as *le territoire*.

fields.Title: You: "Sounds invigorating."
fields.Dialogue Text: Sounds invigorating.

fields.Title: You: "What's this book about?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What's this book about?

fields.Title: You: "I think I've heard enough."
fields.Dialogue Text: I think I've heard enough.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "You close the book and return it to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You close the book and return it to its place on the shelf.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "Suddenly, as if out of nowhere, a s..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Suddenly, as if out of nowhere, a small green book becomes apparent. The title of it reads: "Medicinal Purposes of the Pale."

fields.Title: You: "What else?"
fields.Dialogue Text: What else?

fields.Title: Tutorial Agent: "You've acquired an interactable ite..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You've acquired an interactable item. Investigate this item further by going to the INTERACT tab in your INVENTORY.

fields.Title: You: "Does the book say anything else?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Does the book say anything else?

fields.Title: You: "I probably need that."
fields.Dialogue Text: I probably need that.

fields.Title: Inland Empire: "The throbbing in your head increase..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The throbbing in your head increases with every passing moment you gaze at this shelf...

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "For example, it recommends vigorous..."
fields.Dialogue Text: For example, it recommends vigorously swatting one's naked body with a venik, or hand broom, made from "the leafy twigs of a young birch tree from the near-pale."

fields.Title: You: "Huh. Anything else of note?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Huh. Anything else of note?

fields.Title: You: "How is that possible?"
fields.Dialogue Text: How is that possible?

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "These strolls promise to "cleanse t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: These strolls promise to "cleanse the mind of worries and the body of toxins," especially if the perambulator performs this ritual in the nude. (Nudity figures prominently in a number of these prescriptions.)

fields.Title: Plaisance: ""Well, I hope it contains what you'..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Well, I hope it contains what you're looking for."

fields.Title: Plaisance: ""Hum... sir, please, no browsing in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hum... sir, please, no browsing in that shelf." She narrows her eyes. "That wisdom is not for free."

fields.Title: Endurance: "It's your own fault if you're ill,..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's your own fault if you're ill, got it.

fields.Title: Jump to: [Shelf of Paranormal Books: "Various paranatural books still lit..."]
Shelf of Paranormal Books: "Is it any more improbable than anyt..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Is it any more improbable than anything else that human beings put their faith in?

fields.Title: You: "Well, I certainly don't need that."
fields.Dialogue Text: Well, I certainly don't need that.

fields.Title: Shelf of Paranormal Books: "There's an entire section devoted t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: There's an entire section devoted to cures for men who are struggling to perform their "marital obligations."
